userestrict.head: Publication Rights
userestrict.p: Property rights reside with the repository. Literary rights reside with the creators of the documents or their heirs. To obtain permission to publish or reproduce, please contact the Public Services Librarian of the Dept. of Special Collections.

acqinfo.head: Acquisition Information
acqinfo.p: Gift of James A. Healy in memory of his wife Josephine, 1975.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: James Healy's The literary renaissance and politics of Ireland : ephemera. M1138. Dept. of Special Collections, Stanford University Libraries, Stanford, Calif.

bioghist.head: Biography
bioghist.p: James Augustine Healy was a stockbroker and bibliophile who collected books, letters and manuscripts in the area of Irish literature and politics. He collected from the 1930s until the time of his death in 1975.

scopecontent.head: Collection Scope and Content Summary
scopecontent.p: Correspondence relating to the building of his book and manuscript collection, subject files, articles, publications, photographs, etc.

controlaccess.head: Access Terms
controlaccess.p: The following terms have been used to index the description of this collection in the library's online public access catalog.
